# Z-Sanctuary: Control root awareness (Z-CONTROL-LINK-1)

**Z-CONTROL-LINK-1 is sealed on `main`.** Treat **`Z_Sanctuary_Universe` (this hub repo)** as the **canonical governance and control root** for Z-Sanctuary satellite project links. Long doctrine, registries, and verification authority live here—not duplicated across siblings.

## Z-CYCLE-OBSERVE-1 (Z-CURSOR-AWARENESS-3)

**Z-CYCLE-OBSERVE-1 is sealed** as the **continuous observation tower** and **safe task-queue layer** for the ecosystem (see [`docs/Z_CYCLE_OBSERVE_SYSTEM.md`](docs/Z_CYCLE_OBSERVE_SYSTEM.md), `npm run z:cycle:observe`).

- The observer **writes only** `data/reports/z_cycle_observe_status.{json,md}` and **generates** a `task_queue` — it **does not execute** queued tasks.
- **`overall_observer_signal` BLUE** means **informational / governed awareness** (e.g. drift or sequencing posture in the rollup), **not** “failure” and **not** permission to auto-repair or auto-deploy.
- **Cursor** may read that report and **suggest** the next **`cursor/zsanctuary/…`** Turtle Mode branch; **AMK / human** chooses which queue line (if any) becomes work.
- **Cursor must not:** auto-run queue items; deploy; merge; push; install packages; start services; mutate NAS; connect real devices; repair files automatically; or touch secrets.
- **Workflow stays:** small branch → verify gates → human review → merge. This awareness update adds **no new autonomous authority**.

## Z-PC-ACTIVATION-AWARENESS-1 (operator PowerShell / hub session receipt)

After AMK uses the **Z_Sanctuary_Universe** shell route (PowerShell or manual `npm` from hub root), **`npm run z:pc:activation`** may be run to refresh **`data/reports/z_pc_activation_receipt.{json,md}`** — a **local read-only** snapshot (git branch/HEAD/status, phase green-receipt mtimes, verify script sample, on-disk report signals, sealed systems, Turtle posture). The receipt script **does not** run verify pipelines unless a future human-approved phase says otherwise.

- **When starting work**, Cursor should **check** `z_pc_activation_receipt.md` (or `.json`) to see what the operator **recently activated** on this clone.
- Cursor **may** summarize that receipt and **suggest** a **`cursor/zsanctuary/…`** Turtle Mode branch — **visibility only**.
- Cursor **must not** treat the receipt as **permission to execute** queued tasks, verify scripts, merge, deploy, or mutate NAS — **AMK / human** still chooses the next lane.

Full doc: [`docs/Z_PC_ACTIVATION_AWARENESS.md`](docs/Z_PC_ACTIVATION_AWARENESS.md).

## Z-DEPLOYMENT-READINESS-OVERSEER-1 (read-only deployment posture rollup)

**Z-DEPLOYMENT-READINESS-OVERSEER-1** adds `npm run z:deployment:readiness` → `scripts/z_deployment_readiness_status.mjs`, which writes only **`data/reports/z_deployment_readiness_status.{json,md}`** from hub registries and existing report JSON. It **does not** deploy, bind edge, merge, execute the Cycle Observe queue, install packages, scan arbitrary disks, or touch secrets. Cursor may **read** the rollup to **suggest** Turtle branches — **AMK / human** still chooses every build, merge, deploy, and external action.

Full doc: [`docs/Z_DEPLOYMENT_READINESS_OVERSEER.md`](docs/Z_DEPLOYMENT_READINESS_OVERSEER.md).

## Satellites

- Satellites carry **one thin bridge file** only: `docs/Z_SANCTUARY_CONTROL_LINK.md` (relative to each satellite root), aligned from the hub template of the same path.
- **Approved targets** live in [`data/z_satellite_control_link_manifest.json`](data/z_satellite_control_link_manifest.json). Do not assume a folder is a satellite until it appears there with intentional `enabled` / `status`.

## Sync (operator tooling)

- Hub script: [`scripts/z_sync_control_links.mjs`](scripts/z_sync_control_links.mjs).
- **`npm run z:control-links:dry`** — default **dry-run** (plan / compare; writes hub sync **reports** only under `data/reports/`).
- **`npm run z:control-links:apply`** — writes the bridge markdown **only** to manifest-approved destinations; use only after human review.

## Hard boundaries for AI and automation

- **Do not** scan arbitrary PC folders or enumerate drives outside the manifest-driven loop in `z_sync_control_links.mjs`.
- **Do not** write bridge or governance files **outside** manifest-approved target paths.
- **Do not** deploy, bind domains, write or rotate secrets, install IDE extensions, start background services, or mutate NAS trees from this control-link lane.
- **NAS** rows stay **`NAS_WAIT`** (manifest + script) until the path is mounted, verified, and an operator enables them cautiously.

